title: 'Very important we listen to the DUP,' says Irish PM with Windsor Framework still in balance
description: The Irish prime minister has played down the need for the UK government to alter the new UK-EU post-Brexit deal, despite the DUP calling for it to be "changed".

title: Hezbollah could be linked to explosion in northern Israel that injured civilian
description: Israeli military and intelligence believe the Lebanese militant organisation Hezbollah could be linked to an explosion in northern Israel on Monday which severely injured an Arab-Israeli civilian.

title: Suspect killed and six police officers injured in house explosion during arrest - reports
description: At least six police officers have been injured, including three seriously, in a house explosion in France, according to media reports.

title: More than 100 arrested over mystery gas incidents at girls' schools in Iran
description: Iranian authorities have arrested more than 100 people in connection with a recent wave of suspected poisonings of schoolgirls across the country, believed to have been an attempt to stop them from attending school.

title: Imran Khan accused of 'blatant lies' by Pakistan minister as police and supporters clash
description: Pakistan's Information Minister has accused Imran Khan of "uttering blatant lies" and denied the attempts to arrest him are politically motivated.

title: Arrest of Imran Khan halted after violence - as he claims it was bid to 'abduct and assassinate' him
description: An operation to arrest Pakistan's former prime minister Imran Khan has been suspended after a court ruling.

title: Leonardo da Vinci was the son of a slave and half-Italian, expert claims
description: Mona Lisa painter Leonardo da Vinci was only half-Italian and his mother was a slave who was trafficked to Italy from the Caucasus region, new research has claimed.

title: Five killed after flooding in earthquake-hit regions of Turkey
description: Five people were killed and several more are missing after floods struck two provinces in Turkey that were devastated by last month's earthquakes.

title: FTSE 100 takes £75bn hit as Europe becomes new focus of Silicon Valley Bank fallout
description: The FTSE 100 and other major European stock markets have taken a beating as concern over the health of US banks crosses the Atlantic.

title: Vienna police warn of potential Islamist terror attack on churches
description: Police in Vienna have said more armed officers will be on the streets after intelligence suggested a possible terror attack was being planned against churches.

title: What do we know about the US drone crash involving a Russian jet?
description: The US and Russia have different accounts of what caused an American drone to crash into the Black Sea on Tuesday.

title: Russian aircraft intercepted by RAF and German air force in first of its kind NATO mission
description: A Russian aircraft has been intercepted by British RAF and German fighter jets after it was identified near NATO airspace.
